// VM smoke (issue 04): the host arch-secure profile — SOPS + impermanence + ZFS
// native encryption on a 2-disk mirror — installed headlessly through the test
// flow, exercising the object-form post_install.{security,backup} (ADR 0041).
//   vm.sh --testing --profile headless/secure        (install-only)
//
// Install-only — NOT --verify-boot: a ZFS native-encrypted root prompts for the
// passphrase at boot (keylocation=prompt) and the headless boot-verify cannot
// type it (cf. single/guided-secure, impermanence/kde-encrypted). The smoke
// asserts the secure stack assembles + installs to ===INSTALLER-EXIT-0===; the
// daemons-enabled assertion is covered headlessly by single/guided-extras (same
// resolver → Runner paru pass).
//
// host_profile arch-secure carries the object-form Security & Backup Extras
// (firewalld + clamav + rkhunter + apparmor and zfs-auto-snapshot + borg), which
// install via the Primary User's (vm-test) paru pass. The test flow exports
// INSTALL_ENC_PASSPHRASE='testtest' + SECRETS_AGE_PASSPHRASE='test'; the fixture
// HTTP server serves the Test Age Key the Secrets Module fetches at
// http://192.168.122.1:9876/key.age.
{
  "name": "arch-zfs-test-secure",
  "hardware": { "disks": [40, 40], "ram_mb": 6144, "vcpus": 4 },
  "timeouts": { "install": 4200 },
  "host_profile": "arch-secure",
  "fixtures": ["fixtures/key.age"]
}
